description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated person to work in an Integrated Health and Social care team as a community staff nurse in Usk and Raglan. You will participate in delivering care within the progressive environment of an integrated health and social care model, caring for people in their own environments.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will become a member of an experienced, supportive team who will help you in acquiring and utilising new skills. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will possess a flexible attitude and a caring, person centred and professional approach to patient care, enjoying working on your own as well as being a team player.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Renee Dotson or Ceri James, Team Manager&lt;br /&gt;Renee.dotson@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;01633 644301&lt;/p&gt;
